SIMPLE: peregrinate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peregrinate
<hw>Per"e*gri*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peregrinatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>peregrinari</ets> to travel. See
<er>Pilgrim</er>.]</ety> <def>To travel from place to place, or from one
country to another; hence, to sojourn in foreign countries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peregrinate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Peregrinate
<hw>Per"e*gri*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peregrinatus</ets>, p. p.]</ety> <def>Having traveled;
foreign.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peregrination</ent>⟦br⟧
